(9957, 78, '_components_4_header_graphic', 'field_593efe8bf9f9a_field_59b6dea54de66'),
(9958, 78, 'components_4_header', 'ENERGY & WATER'),
(9959, 78, '_components_4_header', 'field_593efe8bf9f9a_field_59b6de9f4de65'),
(9960, 78, 'components_4_body_copy', 'Industrial paper mills are a significant global consumer of energy and water. Yet Preserve stands alone by using the least possible amount of energy in its paper production. We use run-off water from local farms to make our pulp, drying our natural paper in the beautiful open fields in India.\r\n\r\nMore than that, we create centralized manufacturing production units that consolidate sourcing and transportation and save fuel used for transport. We also deploy a highly streamlined supply chain process built on absolute efficiency, conserving resources wherever possible. From papermaking to packaging to production and beyond, we are committed to being green.'),
